commit.message:
GUACAMOLE-422: Replace non-short-circuit logic in null check (`&`) with proper short-circuit logic (`&&`).

Checking `timezone != null & !timezone.isEmpty()` will result in a
`NullPointerException` when `timezone` is null, as the `&` ensures
`timezone.isEmpty()` will run in all cases.
GUACAMOLE-580: Avert potential NullPointerException when looking for user attributes.
GUACAMOLE-362: Avoid NullPointerException when closing input stream.
GUAC-586: Fix potential NullPointerExceptions in basic and LDAP auth.
GUAC-1115: Fix NPE in password conversion.

Merge pull request #102 from glyptodon/group-rest-npe

GUAC-1108: Use retrieval service for retrieving connection groups. Avoid possible NPE.
GUAC-969: Fix possible NPE in reading of local environment.
GUAC-969: Fix possible NPE in XML parsing.
Handle possible NPE in mapping loader.
Fix possible NPE in MonitoringGuacamoleReader read() and readInstruction().
Ticket #269: Fix NPE in connection record re: dates.
GUAC-1108: Use retrieval service for retrieving connection groups. Avoid possible NPE.
Clean up auth provider code, avoid NPE with property. Use getRequiredProperty() for required property.
Fixing NPE found when not having required host and port properties.
Fix NPE if end-of-stream encountered during handshake (fixes #195).
GUAC-969: Fix possible NPE in GuacamoleClassLoader, if the contents of the lib directory cannot be listed.
Fixed NPE in reader when connection closed during negotiaion. Added getRequiredProperty().

Merge pull request #311 from glyptodon/login-npe

GUAC-1442: Do not attempt to remove/retrieve tokens that do not exist.
